  "root_text": {
    "iti95:0.1": "Itivuttaka 95 ",
    "iti95:0.2": "Tikanipāta ",
    "iti95:0.3": "Pañcamavagga ",
    "iti95:0.4": "Kāmūpapattisutta ",
    "iti95:1.1": "Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti95:2.1": "“Tisso imā, bhikkhave, kāmūpapattiyo. ",
    "iti95:2.2": "Katamā tisso? ",
    "iti95:2.3": "Paccupaṭṭhitakāmā, nimmānaratino, paranimmitavasavattino—",
    "iti95:2.4": "imā kho, bhikkhave, tisso kāmūpapattiyo”ti. ",
    "iti95:2.5": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti95:2.6": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti95:3.1": "“Paccupaṭṭhitakāmā ca, ",
    "iti95:3.2": "ye devā vasavattino; ",
    "iti95:3.3": "Nimmānaratino devā, ",
    "iti95:3.4": "ye caññe kāmabhogino; ",
    "iti95:3.5": "Itthabhāvaññathābhāvaṁ, ",
    "iti95:3.6": "saṁsāraṁ nātivattare. ",
    "iti95:4.1": "Etamādīnavaṁ ñatvā, ",
    "iti95:4.2": "kāmabhogesu paṇḍito; ",
    "iti95:4.3": "Sabbe pariccaje kāme, ",
    "iti95:4.4": "ye dibbā ye ca mānusā. ",
    "iti95:5.1": "Piyarūpasātagadhitaṁ, ",
    "iti95:5.2": "chetvā sotaṁ duraccayaṁ; ",
    "iti95:5.3": "Asesaṁ parinibbanti, ",
    "iti95:5.4": "asesaṁ dukkhamaccaguṁ. ",
    "iti95:6.1": "Ariyaddasā vedaguno, ",
    "iti95:6.2": "sammadaññāya paṇḍitā; ",
    "iti95:6.3": "Jātikkhayamabhiññāya, ",
    "iti95:6.4": "nāgacchanti punabbhavan”ti. ",
    "iti95:7.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti95:7.2": "Chaṭṭhaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti95:0.1": "So It Was Said 95 ",
    "iti95:0.2": "The Book of the Threes ",
    "iti95:0.3": "Chapter Five ",
    "iti95:0.4": "Provided With Pleasure ",
    "iti95:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti95:2.1": "“Mendicants, there are these three ways of being provided with sensual pleasures. ",
    "iti95:2.2": "What three? ",
    "iti95:2.3": "Some sensual pleasures are simply present; some are for those who love to create; and some are for those who control what is created by others. ",
    "iti95:2.4": "These are the three ways of being provided with sensual pleasures.” ",
    "iti95:2.5": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti95:2.6": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti95:3.1": "“Sensual pleasures that are simply present, ",
    "iti95:3.2": "gods who control what is imagined by others, ",
    "iti95:3.3": "gods who love to create, ",
    "iti95:3.4": "and others who indulge in sensual pleasures—",
    "iti95:3.5": "They go from this state to another, ",
    "iti95:3.6": "but don’t escape transmigration. ",
    "iti95:4.1": "Knowing this danger ",
    "iti95:4.2": "in sensual indulgence, an astute person ",
    "iti95:4.3": "would forsake all sensual pleasures, ",
    "iti95:4.4": "both human and heavenly. ",
    "iti95:5.1": "Having cut the stream so hard to pass, ",
    "iti95:5.2": "that’s tied to pleasant seeming things, ",
    "iti95:5.3": "they become fully extinguished, ",
    "iti95:5.4": "completely transcending suffering. ",
    "iti95:6.1": "Seers of the noble truths, knowledge masters, ",
    "iti95:6.2": "the astute, understanding rightly, ",
    "iti95:6.3": "directly know the ending of rebirth, ",
    "iti95:6.4": "they come not back to future lives.” ",
    "iti95:7.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "iti95:2.1": "kāmūpapattiyo → kāmuppattiyo (bj); kāmupapattiyo (pts-vp-pli1) "
  },
